The paper proposes a general approach to modeling semi-supervised learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using Bayesian optimization methods, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DS). The experiments conducted in the paper involve link-based text classification and relation extraction, which are tasks that fall under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
